This is a known breaking change. Android 15 (API 35) removed `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE`, and .NET MAUI 10 enables **edge-to-edge** by default — so the old `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` no longer works.

## The Fix: React to IME (keyboard) WindowInsets

In your Android platform code, use `ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener` to detect the keyboard and adjust your layout's bottom padding:

**Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs**
```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Ensure the soft input mode is set to AdjustNothing —
        // we handle the offset ourselves via insets.
        Window!.SetSoftInputMode(SoftInput.AdjustNothing);

        var rootView = FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;

        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navBarInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use the larger of IME or nav-bar bottom inset
            int bottomPx = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navBarInsets.Bottom);

            view.SetPadding(
                view.PaddingLeft,
                view.PaddingTop,
                view.PaddingRight,
                bottomPx);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

## Why this works

| .NET 9 (old) | .NET 10 (new) |
|---|---|
| `AdjustResize` told the OS to shrink your window | Android 15 ignores this flag |
| Layout resized automatically | You read **IME insets** and apply padding yourself |

## Tips for your chat screen

- **Wrap your message list** in a `CollectionView` or `ScrollView` so it scrolls when the layout shrinks.
- **Call `ScrollTo` on the last message** after the keyboard opens to keep the conversation visible.
- On **iOS**, `AdjustResize` was never used — iOS MAUI already handles keyboard avoidance, so no changes needed there.
